From Chih Keng Chen Subject COntrol SYstems analysis PAcKage COSY PAK updated for Mathematica Announcing COSY PAK A symbolic COntrol SYstems analysis PAcKage Version NO USER FEE RELEASE for Mathematica Version or higher INTRODUCTION COSY PAK is set of packages and notebooks for classical control and some modern state space control analysis and design The notebooks in COSY PAK follow a typical Control Engineering I' course taught at many universities around the world for the junior senior level There is NO FEE to use COSY PAK but certain responsibilities are expected of the user see Copyright notice in the README file included below For starters e mail FAX Mail Post the registration form included in the README COSY PAK is available via anonymous ftp' from INTERNET No in the pub A typical ftp session in UNIX is given after the README FUTURE RELEASES If you would like to receive updates and newer versions of COSY PAK please send e mail FAX mail to the address In addition your comments and suggestions are appreciated and are invaluable to We will do our best to fix any reported However we cannot fix those bugs that have not been reported to us and those we do not know We would very much appreciate you taking a few minutes to communicate to us via e mail US Mail Telephone This will help us to release bug free versions in the Comments are Sreenath Systems Engineering Department Case School of Engineering Case Western Reserve University e mail Mail Sreenath Systems Crawford Hall FAX Case Western Reserve Cleveland OH Begin README file NO USER FEE RELEASE COSY PAK A symbolic COntrol SYstems analysis PAcKage Version for Mathematica Version or higher by Sreenath Systems Engineering Case School of Engineering Case Western Reserve University Cleveland OH e mail Copyright Copyright Copyright by Chen and Sreenath Case Western Reserve Permission to use copy modify and distribute this software and its documentation for any purpose and without fee is hereby granted provided that the 