rol systems methods have been implemented in this This package and the attendant notebooks were developed on a NeXT TM computer a UNIX based workstation They have been used as a supplementary teaching aid along with standard control engineering texts Ogata Phillips and Harbor for undergraduate courses in Control Engineering I' taught at the Systems Engineering Department of In addition to the NeXT they have also been tested successfully on Apple Macintosh computers TM and IBM PC's TM running MS Windows TM We would be very much interested to hear from you if you or anybody you know uses this software on platforms not mentioned IBM users however will have to evaluate the notebooks first to visualize the Once installed see below for instructions this collection of Mathematica packages can be loaded by any Bundled with the packages are many notebooks COSY Notes which demonstrate the functionality of these The notebooks follow a plan of many fine standard undergraduate Control Engineering text books listed in the Examples used in these notebooks have been collected from the various references given at the end of this The contents of the notebooks in the COSY Notes directory are given Begin COSY Notes Contents NOTEBOOK FILE NAME CHAPTER Introduction to Control Systems Sections Analyticity Poles and Zeros Signals Forward Laplace Transforms Inverse Laplace Transforms Differential Equation With Zero Valued Initial Conditions Differential Equation With Initial Conditions NOTEBOOK FILE NAME Math CHAPTER Mathematical Modeling of Dynamic Systems Sections ODE to State Space Linearization of a Nonlinear System of Equations State Space to Transfer Function NOTEBOOK FILE NAME Transient CHAPTER Transient Response Analysis Chapter split into three sub notebooks because of file size NOTEBOOK FILE NAME Transient Sections Time Response Analysis First order System Second Order System Third Order and Higher Order Systems NOTEBOOK FILE NAME Transient Sections First Order System Step Response Time Const NOTEBOOK FILE NAME Transient Sections Second Order System Step Response Damping Ratio NOTEBOOK FILE NAME Steady State CHAPTER Steady State Response Sections Routh's Stability Steady State Error Analysis NOTEBOOK FILE NAME Root CHAPTER Root Locus Analysis NOTEBOOK FILE NAME Freq CHAPTER Frequency Response Analysis Sections Bode Plot Analysis Magnitude Phase Plot Nichols Plot Polar Plot Nyquist Plot Combined Example NOTEBOOK FILE NAME State CHAPTER State Space Methods Sections Introduction State Transition Matrix Controllability Observability Output Controllability Pole Placement Design Observer Design Time Response Using State Space Methods End Notebook Contents Compressed Files The files that contain a complete set of the COSY PAK packages and Notebooks for Mathematica are COSY PAK compressed tar file for Unix systems COSY PAK compressed sit file for Macintosh systems and encoded by BinHex format requires the shareware Stuffit file v or higher COSY PAK IBM zip file for the IBM PC running MS DOS Once expanded the Mathematica files can also be used on Macintosh IBM PC Unix systems Installation of COSY PAK o In UNIX Command line type the following command zcat COSY PAK tar xvf o In Macintosh open the file using the shareware Stuffit v or o In IBM Command line type the following command pkunzip o d COSY PAK IBM NOTE This file was zipped by zip utility You must use pkunzip version or higher to unzip IBM PC's may limit the directory name characters to In that event type pkunzip o d COSY You can also unzip the COSY PAK IBM file on any Unix machine if you have unzip utility on Uncompressing and untarring COSY PAK or unzipping COSY PAK IBM will create a directory called COSY PAK Once the files are expanded you should see a single directory COSY PAK containing the following three files four sub directories and their contents SUB DIRECTORIES in COSY PAK COSYPAK contains control tool box packages MANUAL COSY PAK manual in and COSY Notes contains notebooks For contains Laplace transform package from Mathematica For Mathematica FILES in directory COSYPAK FILES in directory COSY Notes Math Transient Transient Transient Steady State Root Freq State FILES in directory For SUB DIRECTORIES in COSY PAK Common FILES in directory Common Important The notebook example files files will be under the COSY Notes To use the notebooks move the directory COSYPAK' to a directory that Mathematica can recognize LocalLibrary Mathematica Packages on a UNIX machine MY HardDisk Mathematica Packages on an Apple Macintosh c winmath packages on an IBM At the beginning of the Initialization cell of each notebook in COSY Notes directory we list the example about how to make Mathematica identify the directory Initialization of Path Example For a UNIX machine Default Path Join Path LocalLibrary Mathematica Packages Example For an Apple Macintosh Path Join Path MY HardDisk Mathematica Packages Example For IBM PC Path Join Path c winmath packages Change the pathname according to your machine by removing the Mathematica comment sign ' and ' before and after Path' This command makes Mathematica recognize the directory LocalLibrary Mathematica Packages on a UNIX machine MY HardDisk Mathematica Packages on a Apple Macintosh c winmath packages on an IBM PC Mathematica users We include the LaplaceTransform package from Mathematica in the directory For Please move all files and directory under For into the Calculus directory under Mathematica Packages Getting started After installation start Mathematica and open the notebooks in the COSY Notes All notebooks load their own Navigate in the notebooks and IBM users however will have to evaluate the notebooks to visualize the USER RESPONSIBILITIES We request you to take a few minutes and fill out the information below and mail it to us by e mail FAX This will help us to keep your abreast of the improvements and release new versions of COSY Suggestions for improvements are cut here YOUR NAME ORGANIZATION TITLE e mail POST